---
/**
 * @file terms.astro
 * @description Terms of Use page detailing independent project status and disclaimer.
 */

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
	title="Terms of Use: mapaPH" 
	description="Read the complete Terms of Use for mapaPH. Learn about open-source licenses, data warnings, and disclaimer of warranty."
>
	<Navbar />

	<main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 text-mapa-ink">
		<article>
			<span class="font-sans text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-mapa-green">
				Legal
			</span>
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-mapa-green tracking-tight sm:text-5xl font-serif mt-2">
				Terms of Use
			</h1>
			
			<p class="font-sans text-xs text-mapa-clay mt-2">
				Last updated: July 15, 2026
			</p>

			<div class="mt-10 border-t border-mapa-contour/60 pt-8">
				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4">
					1. Acceptance of terms
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					By accessing and browsing the mapaPH hub (mapaph.com) or using any of our linked tools, you agree to comply with and be bound by these Terms of Use. If you do not agree to these terms, you should not access or use the site.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					2. Description of the service
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					mapaPH is an independent, community-driven hub that catalogs open-source utilities built around maps of the Philippines. Each tool listed in our directory is built as a separate application, hosted on its own repository and subdomain.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					3. Independence disclaimer
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					mapaPH is a personal, independent project developed and run by an individual. We are not officially affiliated with, endorsed by, or representing any government agency, municipal office, or official institution of the Republic of the Philippines (such as the Philippine Statistics Authority or the Commission on Elections), despite using public geographic and census data.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					4. Intellectual property and licensing
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					The source code for the hub and all our subprojects is open source and published under the MIT License. You are free to inspect, download, modify, and redistribute the code in accordance with the MIT License terms. The original site layouts, copy, and specific visual branding elements are owned by the project creator.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					5. Warranty disclaimer
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					All tools, services, maps, and geographic datasets are provided strictly on an as-is and as-available basis, without warranties of any kind, either express or implied. Because this project is maintained on a volunteer basis, we do not guarantee that the tools will be accurate, error-free, uninterrupted, or secure. We reserve the right to alter, take offline, or discontinue any application or subdomain without notice.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					6. Limitation of liability
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, the project creator and contributors shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages resulting from the use of or the inability to use our tools, including but not limited to transit delays, incorrect routing parameters, or mapping inaccuracies.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					7. User conduct and prohibited uses
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-4">
					You agree to use our tools only for lawful purposes. You are explicitly prohibited from:
				</p>
				<ul class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 list-disc pl-5 mb-6 space-y-2">
					<li>
						Attempting to disrupt or overload our hosting servers or subdomains through automated scraping scripts or denial-of-service tactics.
					</li>
					<li>
						Submitting false, offensive, or malicious datasets to any of our crowdsourced mapping directories.
					</li>
					<li>
						Using our tools or geographical exports for any illegal, hazardous, or high-risk activity where spatial errors could lead to physical injury or property damage.
					</li>
				</ul>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					8. Crowdsourced data and content
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Some directories display entries submitted by community contributors. We do not guarantee the validity or accuracy of these listings. We reserve the right to review, edit, or delete any community submissions at our discretion. You should independently verify any information (such as locations, routes, or pet policies) before relying on it.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					9. Third-party links
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					Our site links to external repositories and community sites. We are not responsible for the content, privacy practices, or terms of third-party resources.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					10. Governing law and jurisdiction
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					These terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Republic of the Philippines. Any disputes arising out of these terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of the Philippines.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					11. Changes to these terms
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					We reserve the right to update these terms at any time. Changes will be posted here with an updated revision date listed at the top.
				</p>

				<h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-mapa-ink font-serif mb-4 mt-10">
					12. Contact
				</h2>
				<p class="font-sans text-sm text-mapa-ink/90 leading-relaxed mb-6">
					For questions regarding these terms, you can reach out via email at vrsmagwili@gmail.com or by filing an issue in our public GitHub repository.
				</p>
			</div>
		</article>
	</main>

	<Footer />
</BaseLayout>
